# Somewhat Optimized Matrix Multiplication Library
This project aims to decrease the execution time of multiple independent matrix multiplication operations using pthreads and CUDA to parallelize the execution of these operations. 


## Usage of pthread.h library
This implementation uses pthreads to parallelize the execution of processing each input pair of matricies using the producer and consumer pattern. Since input is recieved from a file, there is 1 producer that will parse inputs from the file to be definied as an inputPair struct type containing all nessescary data needed to complete the operation. These inputPairs are put into a shared buffer as tasks for consumers to execute. The number of consumers is defined by the user.

## CUDA kernel
****WORK IN PROGRES****

## File input requirements
Input file format:
    # rows in 1st matrix, # columns in 1st matrix, # rows in 2nd matrix, # columns in 2nd matrix\n
    row 1 of 1st matrix space seperated\n
    ...
    row n of 1st matrix space seperated\n
    \n
    row 1 of 2nd matrix space seperated\n
    ...
    row n of 2nd matrix space seperated\n
    \n
This pattern can be repeated any amount of times within the file, but the size of input rows are limited by the size of MAX_LINE_SIZE.

## Macros definied in header file
    #define BUFFER_SIZE ...
        - "task" queue for operations
    #define MAX_LINE_SIZE ...
        - MAX_LINE_SIZE - 1 is the maximum amount of characters that will be read from the file
